'''Bannister Truelock''' conspired to assassinate [[George III]] of the United Kingdom in 1800 along with [[James Hadfield]].<ref>{{cite ODNB|id=41013|first=Joel Peter|last=Eigen|title=Hadfield, James}}</ref>

Truelock was a shoemaker and a religious fanatic who prophesied the second coming of Jesus Christ. He also insisted in the belief that the Messiah would be born from his mouth.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Dickens|first=Charles|title=All the Year Round: A Weekly Journal|volume= 17}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Poole|first=Steve|title=The Politics of Regicide in England, 1760-1850: Troublesome Subjects|publisher=Manchester University Press|isbn=0719050359|pages=124}}</ref> In December 1800, he was admitted to [[Bethlem Royal Hospital]] for allegedly persuading [[James Hadfield]] that by shooting George III, Hadfield would bring peace to the world.<ref>{{cite book|last=Andrews|first=Jonathan|title=The History of Bethlem|publisher=Psychology Press, 1997|isbn=0415017734|pages=390}}</ref>

