'''Jamilah bint Adwan''' ({{lang-ar|جميلة بنت عدوان}}), (born about 180 CE) was the ancestor of the [[prophets in Islam|Islamic prophet]] [[Muhammad]] on both his paternal and maternal sides. She was daughter of Adwan ibn [[bariq]] of Banu [[Azd]] of [[Yemen]]. Jamilah was one of [[Malik ibn an-Nadr]]'s wives and bore him [[Quraysh (tribe)|Fihr]] was the progenitor of the [[Quraysh (tribe)|Quraysh]] clan.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=KOzmNQTb7_EC&pg=PA28&lpg=PA28&dq=Adwan+bariq&source=bl&ots=M10QhrcC75&sig=9iMqVDDNX45uxRdhk-wBjSiiE3Y&hl=ar&sa=X&ei=rBM7UIWbGqe_0QX884GACg&ved=0CC0Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Adwan%20bariq&f=false Book Muḥammad at Mecca]،</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=31tscfPF4tkC&pg=PA53&lpg=PA53&dq=bint+Adwan&source=bl&ots=jCtPIDXsFu&sig=M5ISQpy_SB__gUzexLPUc4hFatk&hl=ar&sa=X&ei=yBU7UI22NOWg0QWzpYGoDQ&ved=0CC8Q6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=bint%20Adwan&f=false BookMuhammad, the Messenger of Islam: His Life & Prophecy]،</ref> <ref>[https://books.google.com/books?ei=hBk7UMzaDMKw0QW59oHACQ&hl=ar&id=2uGZAAAAIAAJ&dq=bint+al-Harith+b.+Amr+b.+BARIQ&q=amllah+bint+%27Adwan+della+stirpe+Azdita+dei+Bariq.#search_anchor Book Annali dell'Islām]،</ref>
