{{Use British English|date=August 2017}}
'''Jonathan Isaac Pedley''' (born 1962) is a British authority on wine. He was born in [[Wednesfield]], [[Wolverhampton]], England. As a child he attended the [[Royal Wolverhampton School]] where he was Head Boy in the academic year 1979–80. He was the only son and first of three children born to Isaac Pedley (1920-1971) and Dorothy Pedley (1926-2017).

Pedley went on to read [[biochemistry]] at [[Oxford University|Oxford]] before taking a job with Grants of St James's. He helped re-establish the School of Wine and became a [[Master of Wine]] in 1992.<ref name=Floyd>{{cite book |last=Floyd |first=Keith |title=Floyd Uncorked: A No-Nonsense Guide to French Wine|accessdate=|edition=|year=1998|publisher=Harper Collins Illustrated|location=|isbn=978-0-00-414059-9|oclc=}}</ref>

His other notable activities include TV and video productions with [[Keith Floyd]], lecturing at [[Edith Cowan University]] and acting as a wine consultant to [[Carlsberg Group|Carlsberg-Tetley]].<ref name=Floyd />

